	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001913_0001"><!--pb/@n='27r'--></pb>
<lb/><p rend="center"><placeName><geogName type="feature">Cataracts</geogName></placeName><date when="1863-04-30">30 April
<lb/>1863</date></p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Waller</persName></p>
<lb/><p>The five <term type="tribe">Ajawa</term>
<lb/><foreign xml:lang="und">vel Ichawa aut</foreign>
<lb/><persName>Achawa</persName> would never 
<lb/>have got the canoe 
<lb/>up with three <term type="tribe">Shupanga</term>
<lb/>&amp; <term type="tribe">Quillimanites</term>.  I 
<lb/>gave them a fathom 
<lb/>each. The ruffians 
<lb/>asked <persName>Merikano</persName>! only 
<lb/>think.</p>
<lb/><p>If I understand 
<lb/>rightly you will use 
<lb/>the canoe for a load 
<lb/>up and the boat 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001913_0002"><!--pb/@n='27v'--></pb>
<lb/>is considered yours 
<lb/>after <persName>Ali</persName> &amp; <persName>Mabruck</persName>
<lb/>are taken down - 
<lb/>A large canoe will 
<lb/>be necessary for 
<lb/>the luggage as your 
<lb/>craft is small 
<lb/>I shall send for one 
<lb/>though I think 
<lb/>we may be able 
<lb/>in the course of 
<lb/>next month to 
<lb/>draw our supplies 
<lb/>from the <placeName><region>Lake
<lb/>region</region></placeName>.

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001913_0003"><!--pb/@n='28r'--></pb>
<lb/>I mean to use our 
<lb/>green boat to bring 
<lb/>up rice or any 
<lb/>luxuries that may 
<lb/>have been left for 
<lb/>us in the shape 
<lb/>of salt beef &amp; pork. 
<lb/>This is all of business 
<lb/>I hope <persName>Procter</persName> is 
<lb/>better and if so 
<lb/>perhaps a change 
<lb/>up here might 
<lb/>help him.</p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001913_0004"><!--pb/@n='28v'--></pb>
<lb/><!-- there is nothing on this page.  The writing is very faint and looks to be bleed-through from the recto as well as ink transfer from 27v AJS 12/1 -->
			
